IBADAN- The leadership of the proscribed National Union of Road Transport Workers (NURTW) in Oyo State, yesterday raised an alarm of plot to arrest some of its members on trumped up charges. The union in a statement signed by its Chairman, Alhaji Abideen Olajide (Ejiogbe), and made available to journalists in Ibadan on Tuesday evening, said since what he termed illegal proscription of the union by the state government, his members have continued to be law abiding, stating that the union believed in fighting its course through the law courts. According to him, the union has it on good authority that there is a plan to use the police to arrest and detain prominent members of the union through the support of the leadership of park management system in the state, warning that such plan led to the Wild Wild West unrest in the Western region and eventual fall of the first republic. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! Olajide then appealed to the Inspector General of Police, the leadership of other security agencies in the state, prominent indigenes such as royal fathers and religious leaders to prevail on those behind the plot not to drag members of the union into any crisis as it has no intention to distrupt the peace in the state. He maintained that members of the union would never forment trouble but rather be law abiding, with an appeal to the state government to let sleeping dog lie in the state. CSOs Protest Delay In Report Of Public Hearing On Social Media Bill NNPC Has Powers To Make Running Cost Deductions From Source– Kyari He said, “It has now come to our hearing that the government will start to use the police to unlawfully arrest and detain some prominent members of our union NURTW by using the Park Management’s Staff to lead the police to each individual member’s house to arrest and detain them. “